  ('Open Philanthropy Project','Texas Freedom Network Education Fund',150000,'2018-04-01','month','donation log','Criminal justice reform','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/criminal-justice-reform/texas-freedom-network-education-fund-texas-rising-program','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/criminal-justice-reform','Discretionary grant to support the Texas Rising program. This grant will allow Texas Rising to increase its base of young people (under 30 years old) engaged on criminal justice reform issues. The grant will pay for computers, student stipends, and field staff salaries for activities including convenings, trainings, leadership development, digital organizing, and grassroots organizing.','Chloe Cockburn','United States','Texas',NULL,'2018-04-19','day',NULL,NULL),
