  ('Open Philanthropy Project','The Center for Election Science',598600,'2017-12-01','month','donation log','Politics','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/giving/grants/the-center-for-election-science-general-support','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/other-areas','Grantee is a US-based nonprofit that promotes alternative voting methods to plurality voting, with an emphasis on cardinal methods and a special focus on approval voting. The grant is intended to go toward CES’ general expenses over the next year such as salaries, marketing, office supplies, as well as its Ballot Initiative Education Campaign project.','William MacAskill','2018-01-23','day','https://groups.google.com/a/openphilanthropy.org/forum/#!topic/newly.published/5XHsBDrlA3Q',NULL),
